            "authors": "Anastasiou, Charalampos, Cancino, Julián, Chavez, Federico, Duhr, Claude, Lazopoulos, Achilleas, Mistlberger, Bernhard et al.",
            "description": "One-loop integral family T_1 for the NLO and NNLO QCD corrections to q qbar → gamma* gamma*. The family has 4 propagators D_1,...,D_4 (subset of the two-loop family T_2) forming a massless one-loop box with two adjacent off-shell external legs. Two momentum routings used. IBP reduction yields 3 master integrals: bubble (T_1(1,0,1,0)), triangle (T_1(1,0,1,1)), and box (T_1(1,1,1,1)). Bubble is trivial. Triangle result involves the single-valued Bloch-Wigner functions P_2(z) and Q_3(z), expressed through order eps^2. Box result includes the basis functions R_3^+(z,w), P_3(z), P_3(1-z), and Li_3 functions of u/w, v/w, w/u, w/v ratios, given through order eps. All results valid in Euclidean region (s,t,p3^2,p4^2 < 0); analytic continuation to physical region (s,p3^2,p4^2 > 0, t < 0) performed via w → e^{i*pi}*wbar with wbar = -t/s > 0.",
